<statement>
<p>Solve this system of equations using substitution.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}-{2}{y}=-{78}</m> </p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{9}{x}-{8}{y}={48}</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="8" /></p>

</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li><m>\displaystyle{\left({8},{3}\right)}</m></li></ul></p><p>We chose (for no special reason) to solve the first equation for <m>\displaystyle{x}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+-{2}{y}=-{78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}=-{78}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=\frac{{-{78}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p>Then we can substitute this into the second equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{9}{\left(\frac{{-{78}-{\left(-{2}{y}\right)}}}{{-{{9}}}}\right)}+-{8}{y}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle\frac{{9}}{{-{{9}}}}\cdot{\left(-{78}\right)}-\frac{{9}}{{-{{9}}}}{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{78}-{\left(-{2}\right)}{y}+-{8}{y}={48}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}={48}-{78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{2}{y}+{\left(-{8}\right)}{y}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\left(-{2}+{\left(-{8}\right)}\right)}{y}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{10}{y}=-{30}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}=-\frac{{30}}{{-{{10}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{y}={3}</m></p>
<p>Finally we can substitute this y value into the first equation to solve for x.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+-{2}{\left({3}\right)}=-{78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}+{\left(-{6}\right)}=-{78}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}=-{78}-{\left(-{6}\right)}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle-{9}{x}=-{72}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}=-\frac{{72}}{{-{{9}}}}</m></p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{x}={8}</m></p>
<p>Thus the answer is <m>\displaystyle{\left({8},{3}\right)}</m>.</p>

</solution>
</myopenmath>

